  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nGoerli nodes are logging errors like:\r\n\r\n> Jan 29 07:10:17.333 ERRO Unable to validate attestation          error: ObservedAttestationsError(SlotTooLow { slot: Slot(7500292), lowest_permissible_slot: Slot(7500317) }), peer_id: 16Uiu2HAmAPYzUpmcob9r7oJjPsqVnSGkj4LqGejcLQ7S1fJrkQ8D, type: \\\"aggregated\\\", slot: Slot(7500292), beacon_block_root: 0xa2cb85cd686034988c3d9d3540fcd0d1a921016d2b93620d8b0861ac5c2148cc\r\n\r\nAttestations have an increased validity window of prev + current epoch with Deneb, and it seems this is likely caused by the attestation observation cache being undersized here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/1be5253610dc8fee3bf4b7a8dc1d01254bc5b57d/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/observed_aggregates.rs#L44-L47\r\n\r\nWe should probably bump that max size to `2 * SLOTS_PER_EPOCH`.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v4.6.0\r\n\r\n## Additional Info\r\n\r\nThere is also a `SlotTooLow` error in the naive aggregation pool, but I don't think it's implicated because the capacity of that cache is only 3 slots and the errors we're seeing are for slots >32 slots ago.\r\n",
